{"config":{"lang":["ja"],"separator":"[\\s\\-\u3000\u3001\u3002\uff0c\uff0e]+","pipeline":["stemmer"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"\ud83c\uddef\ud83c\uddf5 My Japanese Notes","text":"<p>Personal Japanese vocabulary notes generated by my Telegram bot.</p> <p>Each note includes: - \u5206\u8a5e\u89e3\u6790 (word breakdown) - \u610f\u601d (meaning) - \u4f8b\u53e5 (example sentence) - \u51fa\u5178 (source) - \u53c2\u8003 (references)</p>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/","title":"Troubleshooting Notes","text":""},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#1-jamdict-data-installation-winerror-32","title":"1. jamdict-data Installation \u2014 WinError 32","text":"<p>Error:</p> <pre><code>[WinError 32] \u7a0b\u5e8f\u7121\u6cd5\u5b58\u53d6\u6a94\u6848\uff0c\u56e0\u70ba\u6a94\u6848\u6b63\u7531\u53e6\u4e00\u500b\u7a0b\u5e8f\u4f7f\u7528\u3002: 'jamdict_data/jamdict.db.xz'\n</code></pre> <p>Cause: Windows Defender locks the <code>.xz</code> file during extraction.</p> <p>Fix: - Temporarily disable Windows Defender real-time protection during installation - Or download <code>jamdict.db.xz</code> directly from Google Drive and extract manually with 7-Zip:   https://drive.google.com/drive/u/1/folders/1z4zF9ImZlNeTZZplflvvnpZfJp3WVLPk - Put extracted <code>jamdict.db</code> in <code>jamdictdb/jamdict.db</code></p>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#2-jamdict-cannot-open-database","title":"2. jamdict Cannot Open Database","text":"<p>Error:</p> <pre><code>sqlite3.OperationalError: unable to open database file\n</code></pre> <p>Cause 1: Wrong parameter name \u2014 use <code>db_file</code> not <code>db_path</code>:</p> <pre><code># wrong\njam = Jamdict(db_path=\"...\")\n\n# correct\njam = Jamdict(db_file=\"...\")\n</code></pre> <p>Cause 2: Folder and file have the same name:</p> <pre><code>jamdict.db/        \u2190 folder\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 jamdict.db     \u2190 actual file\n</code></pre> <p>Use the full nested path:</p> <pre><code>jam = Jamdict(db_file=str(BASE_DIR / \"jamdictdb\" / \"jamdict.db\"))\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#3-git-not-found-in-powershell","title":"3. Git Not Found in PowerShell","text":"<p>Error:</p> <pre><code>git : \u7121\u6cd5\u8fa8\u8b58 'git' \u8a5e\u5f59\n</code></pre> <p>Cause: Git was installed after PowerShell was opened, so PATH wasn't updated.</p> <p>Fix: - Close and reopen PowerShell - Or add Git to PATH permanently:</p> <pre><code>[System.Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable(\"PATH\", $env:PATH + \";C:\\Program Files\\Git\\cmd\", \"User\")\n</code></pre> <ul> <li>Note: In PowerShell use <code>where.exe git</code> not <code>where git</code></li> </ul>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#4-git-not-found-in-vscode-terminal","title":"4. Git Not Found in VSCode Terminal","text":"<p>Error:</p> <pre><code>FileNotFoundError: [WinError 2] \u7cfb\u7d71\u627e\u4e0d\u5230\u6307\u5b9a\u7684\u6a94\u6848\n</code></pre> <p>Cause: VSCode terminal doesn't inherit updated system PATH.</p> <p>Fix \u2014 add to VSCode settings.json:</p> <pre><code>{\n    \"terminal.integrated.env.windows\": {\n        \"PATH\": \"C:\\\\Program Files\\\\Git\\\\cmd;${env:PATH}\"\n    }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Or hardcode the path directly in the bot:</p> <pre><code>GIT = r\"C:\\Program Files\\Git\\cmd\\git.exe\"\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#5-github-file-size-limit","title":"5. GitHub File Size Limit","text":"<p>Error:</p> <pre><code>remote: error: File jamdictdb/jamdict.db is 310.32 MB; this exceeds GitHub's file size limit of 100.00 MB\n</code></pre> <p>Cause: <code>jamdictdb/</code> was not in <code>.gitignore</code> before first commit.</p> <p>Fix:</p> <pre><code>git rm -r --cached jamdictdb/\ngit filter-repo --path jamdictdb/ --invert-paths --force\ngit remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo.git\ngit push origin master --force\n</code></pre> <p>Make sure <code>.gitignore</code> contains:</p> <pre><code>jamdictdb/\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#6-token-accidentally-pushed-to-github","title":"6. Token Accidentally Pushed to GitHub","text":"<p>Cause: <code>.env</code> was not in <code>.gitignore</code> before first commit.</p> <p>Fix: 1. Revoke token immediately via @BotFather \u2192 <code>/mybots</code> \u2192 Revoke token 2. Remove from Git history:</p> <pre><code>python -m git_filter_repo --path .env --invert-paths --force\ngit remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo.git\ngit push origin master --force\n</code></pre> <ol> <li>Create new <code>.env</code> with new token</li> <li>Make sure <code>.gitignore</code> contains <code>.env</code></li> </ol>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#7-git-filter-repo-not-recognized","title":"7. git filter-repo Not Recognized","text":"<p>Error:</p> <pre><code>git: 'filter-repo' is not a git command\n</code></pre> <p>Fix:</p> <pre><code>pip install git-filter-repo\npython -m git_filter_repo --path .env --invert-paths --force\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#8-wrong-branch-name","title":"8. Wrong Branch Name","text":"<p>Error:</p> <pre><code>error: src refspec main does not match any\n</code></pre> <p>Cause: Default branch is <code>master</code> not <code>main</code>.</p> <p>Fix:</p> <pre><code>git branch          \u2190 check current branch name\ngit push -u origin master\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#9-author-identity-unknown","title":"9. Author Identity Unknown","text":"<p>Error:</p> <pre><code>Author identity unknown \u2014 Please tell me who you are.\n</code></pre> <p>Fix:</p> <pre><code>git config --global user.email \"your@email.com\"\ngit config --global user.name \"YourName\"\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#10-run_polling-unexpected-keyword-argument","title":"10. run_polling() Unexpected Keyword Argument","text":"<p>Error:</p> <pre><code>Application.run_polling() got an unexpected keyword argument 'read_timeout'\n</code></pre> <p>Cause: Timeout arguments moved to <code>ApplicationBuilder</code> in newer versions.</p> <p>Fix:</p> <pre><code>app = (\n    ApplicationBuilder()\n    .token(TOKEN)\n    .read_timeout(30)\n    .write_timeout(30)\n    .connect_timeout(30)\n    .pool_timeout(30)\n    .build()\n)\napp.run_polling(\n    allowed_updates=Update.ALL_TYPES,\n    drop_pending_updates=True,\n)\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#11-kotobank-404-error","title":"11. Kotobank 404 Error","text":"<p>Error: Page not found on Kotobank.</p> <p>Cause: Kotobank direct word URLs require an internal ID number.</p> <p>Fix: Use search URL instead:</p> <pre><code># wrong\nhttps://kotobank.jp/word/{word}\n\n# correct\nhttps://kotobank.jp/search/{word}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#12-mkdocs-gh-deploy-git-not-found","title":"12. MkDocs gh-deploy \u2014 Git Not Found","text":"<p>Error:</p> <pre><code>ERROR - Could not find git - is it installed and on your path?\n</code></pre> <p>Fix: Run in Command Prompt instead of PowerShell:</p> <pre><code>conda activate myenv\ncd C:\\Users\\User\\Documents\\Japanese\nmkdocs gh-deploy\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"Problem_shooting/#general-tips","title":"General Tips","text":"<ul> <li>Always run <code>git status</code> before <code>git push</code> to check what files will be committed</li> <li>Use <code>git reset HEAD~1</code> to undo the last commit before pushing</li> <li><code>.env</code> and <code>jamdictdb/</code> should never appear in <code>git status</code> as staged files</li> <li>In PowerShell use <code>where.exe git</code> instead of <code>where git</code></li> <li>Restart VSCode completely after installing new tools for PATH to update</li> </ul>"},{"location":"notes/20260517_132356_%E7%A7%81%E3%81%AF%E4%B8%80%E8%A8%80%E8%A8%80%E3%81%84%E3%81%BE%E3%81%99/","title":"\u79c1\u306f\u4e00\u8a00\u8a00\u3044\u307e\u3059","text":"","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_132356_%E7%A7%81%E3%81%AF%E4%B8%80%E8%A8%80%E8%A8%80%E3%81%84%E3%81%BE%E3%81%99/#original","title":"\u539f\u53e5 (Original)","text":"<p>\u79c1\u306f\u4e00\u8a00\u8a00\u3044\u307e\u3059</p>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_132356_%E7%A7%81%E3%81%AF%E4%B8%80%E8%A8%80%E8%A8%80%E3%81%84%E3%81%BE%E3%81%99/#_2","title":"\u5206\u8a5e\u89e3\u6790","text":"\u8868\u9762\u5f62 \u8b80\u97f3 \u8a5e\u6027 \u539f\u5f62 \u79c1 \u308f\u305f\u304f\u3057 \u4ee3\u540d\u8a5e \u79c1-\u4ee3\u540d\u8a5e \u306f \u306f \u52a9\u8a5e \u306f \u4e00\u8a00 \u3072\u3068\u3053\u3068 \u540d\u8a5e \u4e00\u8a00 \u8a00\u3044 \u3044\u3044 \u52d5\u8a5e \u8a00\u3046 \u307e\u3059 \u307e\u3059 \u52a9\u52d5\u8a5e \u307e\u3059","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_132356_%E7%A7%81%E3%81%AF%E4%B8%80%E8%A8%80%E8%A8%80%E3%81%84%E3%81%BE%E3%81%99/#meaning","title":"\u610f\u601d (Meaning)","text":"<p>\u306f: feather, plume, down \u4e00\u8a00: single word, a few words, brief comment \u8a00\u3046: to say, to utter, to declare \u307e\u3059: measuring container, measure</p>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_132356_%E7%A7%81%E3%81%AF%E4%B8%80%E8%A8%80%E8%A8%80%E3%81%84%E3%81%BE%E3%81%99/#example","title":"\u4f8b\u53e5 (Example)","text":"<p>\u4e00\u8a00\u3067\u8a00\u3046\u3068\u3001</p>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_132356_%E7%A7%81%E3%81%AF%E4%B8%80%E8%A8%80%E8%A8%80%E3%81%84%E3%81%BE%E3%81%99/#source","title":"\u51fa\u5178 (Source)","text":"<p>Massif</p>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_132356_%E7%A7%81%E3%81%AF%E4%B8%80%E8%A8%80%E8%A8%80%E3%81%84%E3%81%BE%E3%81%99/#reference","title":"\u53c2\u8003 (Reference)","text":"<ul> <li>Kotobank</li> <li>Weblio</li> </ul>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_132356_%E7%A7%81%E3%81%AF%E4%B8%80%E8%A8%80%E8%A8%80%E3%81%84%E3%81%BE%E3%81%99/#example-search-attempts","title":"Example Search Attempts","text":"<ul> <li>\u79c1\u306f\u4e00\u8a00\u8a00\u3044\u307e\u3059</li> <li>\u4e00\u8a00</li> </ul>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_132356_%E7%A7%81%E3%81%AF%E4%B8%80%E8%A8%80%E8%A8%80%E3%81%84%E3%81%BE%E3%81%99/#warning","title":"Warning","text":"<p>None</p>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_164807_%E6%9C%9D%E3%81%94%E9%A3%AF%E3%81%8A%E9%A3%9F%E3%81%B9%E3%82%8B/","title":"\u671d\u3054\u98ef\u304a\u98df\u3079\u308b","text":"","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_164807_%E6%9C%9D%E3%81%94%E9%A3%AF%E3%81%8A%E9%A3%9F%E3%81%B9%E3%82%8B/#original","title":"\u539f\u53e5 (Original)","text":"<p>\u671d\u3054\u98ef\u304a\u98df\u3079\u308b</p>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_164807_%E6%9C%9D%E3%81%94%E9%A3%AF%E3%81%8A%E9%A3%9F%E3%81%B9%E3%82%8B/#_2","title":"\u5206\u8a5e\u89e3\u6790","text":"\u8868\u9762\u5f62 \u8b80\u97f3 \u8a5e\u6027 \u539f\u5f62 \u671d\u3054\u98ef \u3042\u3055\u3054\u306f\u3093 \u540d\u8a5e \u671d\u5fa1\u98ef \u304a \u304a \u63a5\u982d\u8f9e \u5fa1 \u98df\u3079\u308b \u305f\u3079\u308b \u52d5\u8a5e \u98df\u3079\u308b","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_164807_%E6%9C%9D%E3%81%94%E9%A3%AF%E3%81%8A%E9%A3%9F%E3%81%B9%E3%82%8B/#meaning","title":"\u610f\u601d (Meaning)","text":"<p>\u671d\u5fa1\u98ef: breakfast</p> <p>\u5fa1: honorific/polite/humble prefix</p> <p>\u98df\u3079\u308b: to eat</p>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_164807_%E6%9C%9D%E3%81%94%E9%A3%AF%E3%81%8A%E9%A3%9F%E3%81%B9%E3%82%8B/#example","title":"\u4f8b\u53e5 (Example)","text":"<p>\u3068\u308a\u3042\u3048\u305a\u3001\u671d\u5fa1\u98ef\u3092\u98df\u3079\u3088\u3046\u304b\u306a</p>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_164807_%E6%9C%9D%E3%81%94%E9%A3%AF%E3%81%8A%E9%A3%9F%E3%81%B9%E3%82%8B/#source","title":"\u51fa\u5178 (Source)","text":"<p>Massif</p>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_164807_%E6%9C%9D%E3%81%94%E9%A3%AF%E3%81%8A%E9%A3%9F%E3%81%B9%E3%82%8B/#reference","title":"\u53c2\u8003 (Reference)","text":"<ul> <li>Kotobank</li> <li>Weblio</li> </ul>","tags":["japanese"]},{"location":"notes/20260517_164807_%E6%9C%9D%E3%81%94%E9%A3%AF%E3%81%8A%E9%A3%9F%E3%81%B9%E3%82%8B/#exam